WEBVTT

00:00:28.871 --> 00:00:30.632
Welcome back to the Yahowah blog.

00:00:30.672 --> 00:00:33.554
For those of you who may be interested

00:00:33.594 --> 00:00:36.896
and notice that we're currently meandering

00:00:36.915 --> 00:00:39.917
back and forth between our rainbow studio

00:00:39.936 --> 00:00:44.598
downstairs and now our library studio up

00:00:44.658 --> 00:00:45.838
here on the pool deck.

00:00:46.859 --> 00:00:48.901
It's because the weather has been quite

00:00:48.941 --> 00:00:51.521
frightful outside here in the Caribbean

00:00:51.601 --> 00:00:54.283
and our ocean studio would be a bit

00:00:54.343 --> 00:00:55.764
problematic until the

00:00:56.723 --> 00:00:58.945
the storminess dies a bit down.

00:00:58.966 --> 00:01:01.127
We're happy to have the blustery

00:01:01.167 --> 00:01:03.609
conditions and the rain,

00:01:04.108 --> 00:01:06.891
which often accompanies it because,

00:01:07.210 --> 00:01:07.450
you know,

00:01:07.471 --> 00:01:11.013
we live on an island and our water

00:01:11.114 --> 00:01:12.534
is what falls on our roof.

00:01:12.875 --> 00:01:13.995
And, you know,

00:01:14.096 --> 00:01:16.537
our electricity is what hits our solar

00:01:16.576 --> 00:01:17.058
panels.

00:01:17.117 --> 00:01:17.878
You know,

00:01:17.897 --> 00:01:21.561
we are very self-sufficient in this kind

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:22.320
of an environment.

00:01:22.822 --> 00:01:24.423
And so we we've become

00:01:25.302 --> 00:01:27.305
fans of the weather,

00:01:27.344 --> 00:01:29.506
but that is what's causing us not to

00:01:29.546 --> 00:01:32.548
go back outside currently into the Ocean

00:01:32.587 --> 00:01:33.049
Studio.

00:01:34.569 --> 00:01:37.231
Here in our library studio,

00:01:37.292 --> 00:01:40.213
we were continuing the story of the last

00:01:40.254 --> 00:01:42.155
Mashal, the last word picture,

00:01:42.534 --> 00:01:43.956
and even though we have finished our

00:01:44.037 --> 00:01:45.778
presentation of

00:01:46.959 --> 00:01:49.762
Mashal, which is a proverb, thirty-one.

00:01:50.822 --> 00:01:53.144
It directed our attention to what had

00:01:53.185 --> 00:01:54.585
caused the intervention,

00:01:54.626 --> 00:01:57.427
because it is the story of a surrogate

00:01:57.468 --> 00:01:59.649
mother visiting with her son,

00:01:59.689 --> 00:02:01.850
and her son is the son of God,

00:02:02.191 --> 00:02:04.072
the Messiah and King, David.

00:02:05.194 --> 00:02:07.835
It led us to the injury that he

00:02:07.855 --> 00:02:10.798
had perpetrated on himself and others that

00:02:11.057 --> 00:02:12.498
required that intervention,

00:02:12.579 --> 00:02:13.439
and that was found in

00:02:14.343 --> 00:02:16.667
In Second Samuel, eleven and twelve,

00:02:16.727 --> 00:02:18.990
and we were at the last statement that

00:02:19.009 --> 00:02:21.513
we're going to review in this regard in

00:02:22.212 --> 00:02:25.336
the twelfth chapter before we move on to

00:02:25.396 --> 00:02:28.881
one of the most painful songs ever

00:02:29.020 --> 00:02:29.342
written.

00:02:30.462 --> 00:02:31.784
Well, I am a.

00:02:33.282 --> 00:02:35.503
celebrant of the Eighty-Ninth Mizmowr.

00:02:35.563 --> 00:02:37.344
I consider it to be the greatest song

00:02:37.384 --> 00:02:37.884
ever written.

00:02:38.985 --> 00:02:41.227
I'm here to tell you that the fifty-first

00:02:41.306 --> 00:02:42.127
may be the worst.

00:02:42.907 --> 00:02:46.348
And it reflects Dowd's mindset at the

00:02:46.368 --> 00:02:46.709
time.

00:02:46.889 --> 00:02:49.770
And I think it's essential that we share

00:02:49.811 --> 00:02:52.912
it so that you know how bad this

00:02:52.951 --> 00:02:54.272
situation had become.

00:02:55.832 --> 00:02:58.715
And it is with great

00:02:59.897 --> 00:03:02.919
respect for our king because he did get

00:03:02.959 --> 00:03:03.639
his act together.

00:03:03.919 --> 00:03:04.500
He recovered.

00:03:05.120 --> 00:03:08.602
He served as the Passover lamb in

00:03:08.662 --> 00:03:09.681
thirty-three CE.

00:03:09.722 --> 00:03:12.503
He carried our guilt into Sheowl,

00:03:13.343 --> 00:03:15.245
deposited there never to be seen again.

00:03:15.284 --> 00:03:17.186
He is the greatest person who has ever

00:03:17.246 --> 00:03:20.826
lived, but he was far from perfect.

00:03:21.507 --> 00:03:22.328
And, you know,

00:03:22.348 --> 00:03:24.209
that is really part of the message of

00:03:24.229 --> 00:03:24.769
this story.

00:03:28.218 --> 00:03:28.959
There are two things.

00:03:29.939 --> 00:03:30.280
Actually,

00:03:30.300 --> 00:03:33.301
there's many things that over the last

00:03:33.382 --> 00:03:35.443
twenty four and a half years that my

00:03:35.463 --> 00:03:37.465
wife and I have been able to deduce

00:03:37.485 --> 00:03:40.467
that no one had seen previously.

00:03:41.008 --> 00:03:44.129
And among them is that Dowd served as

00:03:44.169 --> 00:03:45.811
the Passover lamb in thirty three CE.

00:03:45.950 --> 00:03:48.073
And he made it abundantly clear that that

00:03:48.092 --> 00:03:48.973
was going to be the case.

00:03:48.992 --> 00:03:51.194
And we will find it reinforced throughout

00:03:51.254 --> 00:03:52.955
the hundred and sixteenth Mizmowr,

00:03:52.975 --> 00:03:54.918
which we will review after the fifty

00:03:54.937 --> 00:03:55.217
first.

00:03:56.620 --> 00:03:57.461
That is, I think,

00:03:57.480 --> 00:03:59.301
the greatest discovery in human history,

00:04:00.201 --> 00:04:01.122
pursuant to God,

00:04:01.362 --> 00:04:04.024
because it negates the three Abrahamic

00:04:04.063 --> 00:04:04.525
religions,

00:04:04.564 --> 00:04:08.467
the religions of almost six billion people

00:04:08.687 --> 00:04:09.026
today.

00:04:10.545 --> 00:04:12.287
proving that they are entirely wrong and

00:04:12.306 --> 00:04:14.266
it demonstrates that our Savior,

00:04:14.306 --> 00:04:15.527
the Messiah, the Chosen One,

00:04:15.548 --> 00:04:18.228
the very Son of God is David.

00:04:18.728 --> 00:04:22.810
And it is profoundly important relative to

00:04:22.850 --> 00:04:24.870
our standing with God and to his people's

00:04:25.071 --> 00:04:27.372
standing, Israel's standing with God.

00:04:28.291 --> 00:04:30.533
But this other thing is quite recently,

00:04:30.612 --> 00:04:32.713
we have learned that God has no interest

00:04:32.754 --> 00:04:33.374
in perfection.

00:04:34.249 --> 00:04:36.689
So when somebody is saying that you have

00:04:36.728 --> 00:04:38.189
to be a perfect Passover lamb,

00:04:38.310 --> 00:04:39.629
that's utter nonsense.

00:04:39.689 --> 00:04:41.910
It's the word that is one of the

00:04:41.949 --> 00:04:45.711
most frequently misrepresented in the

00:04:45.771 --> 00:04:47.511
whole of the Towrah prophets and Psalms.

00:04:48.490 --> 00:04:50.692
Tamym doesn't mean perfect.

00:04:50.831 --> 00:04:53.151
It means to complete the job,

00:04:53.211 --> 00:04:56.492
to do what needs to be done to

00:04:56.552 --> 00:04:59.333
finish the mission that you have been

00:04:59.372 --> 00:04:59.872
assigned.

00:05:00.494 --> 00:05:02.074
And Dowd did that.

00:05:03.533 --> 00:05:05.595
recovered in his relationship with Yahowah

00:05:05.694 --> 00:05:08.136
and then proceeded to fulfill the single

00:05:08.196 --> 00:05:11.057
most important mission ever afforded any

00:05:11.197 --> 00:05:11.637
of us,

00:05:11.817 --> 00:05:14.278
and that is the fulfillment of Pesach,

00:05:14.338 --> 00:05:14.598
Matsah,

00:05:14.617 --> 00:05:16.778
and Bikuwrym in year four thousand YAH,

00:05:17.199 --> 00:05:20.379
making him the ideal candidate to do these

00:05:20.420 --> 00:05:25.100
very things because he did what needed to

00:05:25.141 --> 00:05:25.480
be done.

00:05:26.581 --> 00:05:27.302
And so it is

00:05:28.846 --> 00:05:31.788
recognizing this and also recognizing that

00:05:32.129 --> 00:05:35.273
even as we went through Second Samuel,

00:05:36.134 --> 00:05:36.915
eleven and twelve,

00:05:36.975 --> 00:05:38.677
and consider that horrible letter that

00:05:38.697 --> 00:05:40.139
Thaddeus not only wrote,

00:05:40.178 --> 00:05:41.980
but made the man he intended to

00:05:42.100 --> 00:05:45.504
assassinate carry all for the lust of a

00:05:45.545 --> 00:05:45.764
woman.

00:05:48.189 --> 00:05:50.771
Even though we read it because we needed

00:05:50.810 --> 00:05:51.331
to deal with it,

00:05:51.351 --> 00:05:53.273
we never run from anything in the Towrah,

00:05:53.312 --> 00:05:54.014
Prophets and Psalms.

00:05:54.074 --> 00:05:56.134
God clearly detailed it and shared it

00:05:56.196 --> 00:06:00.119
graphically for our understanding.

00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:04.341
We also understand that in context,

00:06:05.403 --> 00:06:07.324
Dowd still remains the most extraordinary

00:06:07.343 --> 00:06:07.824
of all men.

00:06:08.985 --> 00:06:10.067
Prior to this time,

00:06:10.107 --> 00:06:11.908
beginning at eight years of age and

00:06:12.028 --> 00:06:16.151
concluding at fifty-six years of age,

00:06:17.173 --> 00:06:19.915
And Dowd lived the most important forty

00:06:19.956 --> 00:06:22.697
eight years that any human would ever

00:06:22.737 --> 00:06:23.276
experience.

00:06:23.357 --> 00:06:26.738
He was the man for the job.

00:06:27.559 --> 00:06:28.779
He defended his people.

00:06:28.819 --> 00:06:35.002
He wrote marvelous psalms and and he just

00:06:35.023 --> 00:06:37.625
was an exemplar of everything that God was

00:06:37.665 --> 00:06:39.225
striving to achieve with us.

00:06:41.706 --> 00:06:44.848
The fact that he ultimately faltered is

00:06:45.007 --> 00:06:45.189
amazing.

00:06:46.869 --> 00:06:47.028
Well,

00:06:47.048 --> 00:06:48.831
it's something we have to recognize and

00:06:48.870 --> 00:06:49.370
deal with,

00:06:49.430 --> 00:06:53.894
but who of us have lived forty-eight years

00:06:53.935 --> 00:06:54.714
in the spotlight,

00:06:55.315 --> 00:06:56.997
doing the most difficult job in the world,

00:06:57.338 --> 00:06:58.358
representing Yahowah,

00:06:58.939 --> 00:07:03.281
the most highly rejected and demeaned job

00:07:03.742 --> 00:07:05.904
in the world, representing God?

00:07:06.877 --> 00:07:08.317
And he did it for forty-eight years.

00:07:08.338 --> 00:07:09.879
That's longer than anyone else.

00:07:09.899 --> 00:07:12.442
That's eight years longer than Moshe.

00:07:12.461 --> 00:07:12.742
In fact,

00:07:12.762 --> 00:07:14.343
Moshe actually gave up in a year and

00:07:14.483 --> 00:07:16.504
just went through the paces after that

00:07:16.564 --> 00:07:18.726
time.

00:07:19.687 --> 00:07:21.829
It's extraordinary what the man did,

00:07:22.029 --> 00:07:26.814
and we need to keep this in context.

00:07:26.874 --> 00:07:31.959
So Nathan replied to Dowd, Nevertheless,

00:07:33.019 --> 00:07:34.560
Yahowah Abar.

00:07:36.209 --> 00:07:39.910
will one day pass over your chata'ath,

00:07:40.550 --> 00:07:46.951
guilt, through your purifying offering.

00:07:46.971 --> 00:07:49.973
You will never die.

00:07:49.992 --> 00:07:53.293
Samuel, listen to God too, Samuel, twelve,

00:07:53.312 --> 00:07:53.694
thirteen.

00:07:56.113 --> 00:07:59.475
If you pay attention with this being

00:07:59.514 --> 00:08:03.175
stated by Yahowah regarding Dowd,

00:08:05.420 --> 00:08:09.704
then you must acknowledge that there is no

00:08:09.744 --> 00:08:12.887
credibility in Judaism, Christianity,

00:08:13.947 --> 00:08:14.608
or Islam.

00:08:17.009 --> 00:08:18.992
Christianity was the first of those three

00:08:19.091 --> 00:08:20.192
religions to develop.

00:08:21.333 --> 00:08:23.654
And if you read the book of Acts,

00:08:24.036 --> 00:08:26.997
you have both Peter and Paul claiming that

00:08:27.117 --> 00:08:28.019
Dowd was dead.

00:08:29.709 --> 00:08:31.511
And because he was dead,

00:08:32.071 --> 00:08:33.932
they felt at liberty to steal every

00:08:33.971 --> 00:08:36.113
promise Yahowah made about him,

00:08:36.634 --> 00:08:38.894
including his titles, son of God,

00:08:39.554 --> 00:08:42.496
Messiah and King, even savior,

00:08:43.076 --> 00:08:45.717
and give them to their construct,

00:08:46.599 --> 00:08:49.279
their product of identity theft, Jesus.

00:08:50.980 --> 00:08:53.001
But the very fact that it's acknowledged

00:08:53.042 --> 00:08:56.524
here, you will never die.

00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:00.422
means that they lied.

00:09:00.642 --> 00:09:02.462
I know they lied and I make that

00:09:02.503 --> 00:09:04.544
point every time we go downstairs to the

00:09:04.585 --> 00:09:05.705
Rainbow Studio,

00:09:06.025 --> 00:09:08.106
because using Paul's and Peter's own

00:09:08.147 --> 00:09:08.466
words,

00:09:08.486 --> 00:09:12.428
I rip them to shreds and prove that

00:09:12.610 --> 00:09:14.890
there is nothing that they say that is

00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:18.753
rational or true.

00:09:18.793 --> 00:09:19.974
But here it's emphatic,

00:09:20.474 --> 00:09:21.294
you will never die.

00:09:22.054 --> 00:09:24.537
Now with Dowd continuing to live,

00:09:25.477 --> 00:09:29.461
It means that he is the returning Messiah

00:09:29.480 --> 00:09:32.344
and King, just as Yahowah said,

00:09:33.065 --> 00:09:35.005
which means that there is no basis for

00:09:35.066 --> 00:09:37.268
Judaism that claims that an unknown

00:09:37.307 --> 00:09:40.110
Messiah will return to them when in fact

00:09:40.130 --> 00:09:40.530
it's not.

00:09:41.751 --> 00:09:42.192
And of course,

00:09:42.251 --> 00:09:44.332
Christianity would not exist without

00:09:44.493 --> 00:09:47.634
Judaism because the Quran's religiosity is

00:09:47.734 --> 00:09:50.695
all a result of rabbis selling Muhammad

00:09:51.134 --> 00:09:51.875
Talmud readings,

00:09:51.936 --> 00:09:55.557
which he then twisted to suit his

00:09:55.616 --> 00:09:59.057
situation and claimed that they were given

00:09:59.097 --> 00:10:01.318
to him from Allah as opposed to the

00:10:01.359 --> 00:10:03.538
rabbis.

00:10:03.558 --> 00:10:04.340
You will never die.

00:10:05.600 --> 00:10:10.501
It is the line that affirms that I'm

00:10:10.542 --> 00:10:10.761
right.

00:10:13.525 --> 00:10:13.907
that Dowd,

00:10:14.768 --> 00:10:17.750
the one who returned in thirty-three CE,

00:10:17.792 --> 00:10:19.894
year four thousand Yah, to fulfill Pesach,

00:10:19.933 --> 00:10:20.654
Matsah, and Bikuwrym,

00:10:21.576 --> 00:10:22.977
and that it was his soul that carried

00:10:23.018 --> 00:10:23.999
our guilt into Sheowl,

00:10:24.058 --> 00:10:26.982
only to return to the father in Shamaym,

00:10:27.423 --> 00:10:29.725
and that it is Dowd who will return

00:10:29.745 --> 00:10:31.589
to be our king in twenty-thirty-three.

00:10:33.057 --> 00:10:33.918
As for Abar,

00:10:34.599 --> 00:10:36.700
for those who do not know, Abar,

00:10:36.940 --> 00:10:38.059
according to Yahowah,

00:10:38.780 --> 00:10:41.662
as he introduced Passover to us, Pesach,

00:10:42.221 --> 00:10:45.043
he told us that Abar was indeed the

00:10:45.083 --> 00:10:47.125
verbal root of Passover.

00:10:47.644 --> 00:10:49.865
It means to pass over.

00:10:51.547 --> 00:10:52.086
And therefore,

00:10:52.106 --> 00:10:54.587
Abar served to define Passover.

00:10:55.048 --> 00:10:56.408
And Yahowah was saying, nevertheless,

00:10:56.509 --> 00:10:57.429
Yahowah, Abar,

00:10:57.649 --> 00:11:01.591
will pass over one day your chata'ath,

00:11:01.812 --> 00:11:02.072
guilt,

00:11:04.278 --> 00:11:05.798
through your purifying offering,

00:11:06.980 --> 00:11:11.522
which again reaffirms that Dowd will

00:11:11.562 --> 00:11:15.624
resolve his guilt and ours by fulfilling

00:11:16.365 --> 00:11:19.105
Pesach, Matsah, and Bikuwrym.

00:11:20.927 --> 00:11:22.087
All we really have to do is pay

00:11:22.107 --> 00:11:24.188
attention to the words,

00:11:25.129 --> 00:11:27.910
to listen to our God and respond

00:11:28.412 --> 00:11:29.152
intelligently.

00:11:31.690 --> 00:11:32.090
So yes,

00:11:32.210 --> 00:11:35.273
I appreciate Yahowah pointing us to the

00:11:35.352 --> 00:11:37.695
resolution and the restoration of the

00:11:37.735 --> 00:11:40.918
relationship through a bar, which is,

00:11:41.158 --> 00:11:43.259
I have mentioned, but want to underscore,

00:11:44.019 --> 00:11:46.662
is the actionable route of Pesach,

00:11:46.761 --> 00:11:47.383
Passover,

00:11:47.643 --> 00:11:49.565
which is the first day of Chag Matsah.

00:11:50.485 --> 00:11:53.288
Passover is the doorway to life.

00:11:54.067 --> 00:11:54.528
So now...

00:11:56.476 --> 00:11:58.818
All that need be accomplished is to get

00:11:58.879 --> 00:12:02.760
our king back on his feet after having

00:12:02.821 --> 00:12:05.582
fallen so precipitously so that he can

00:12:05.783 --> 00:12:09.225
answer this call and serve as that door.

00:12:11.927 --> 00:12:13.668
So there is another lesson that I want

00:12:13.708 --> 00:12:14.469
to reinforce.

00:12:14.509 --> 00:12:17.451
While Dowd had demonstrated that he was

00:12:17.631 --> 00:12:21.033
not a perfect lamb by religious standards,

00:12:22.135 --> 00:12:24.517
it should now be blatantly obvious that

00:12:25.217 --> 00:12:28.759
Yahowah defines tamym differently than

00:12:28.798 --> 00:12:29.340
do men.

00:12:30.860 --> 00:12:31.280
You see,

00:12:31.860 --> 00:12:34.341
just as we know that God was speaking

00:12:34.442 --> 00:12:38.504
of fulfilling Pesach by interjecting abar

00:12:38.644 --> 00:12:42.005
as its verbal root and then presenting it

00:12:42.145 --> 00:12:45.988
as the answer to death, tamym,

00:12:46.249 --> 00:12:48.850
the word so carelessly rendered perfect,

00:12:50.062 --> 00:12:52.003
is an actionable route.

00:12:53.644 --> 00:12:55.244
Its actionable route is tamam.

00:12:56.124 --> 00:12:57.043
It has one as well.

00:12:57.965 --> 00:13:01.524
We can deduce its meaning, like Pesach,

00:13:01.585 --> 00:13:02.985
meaning to pass over,

00:13:04.546 --> 00:13:06.865
by looking at its actionable route.

00:13:06.985 --> 00:13:09.287
And it speaks of finishing,

00:13:10.626 --> 00:13:11.866
not of being flawless,

00:13:12.687 --> 00:13:14.207
of completing the mission.

00:13:15.589 --> 00:13:17.530
It doesn't say anything about standing

00:13:17.750 --> 00:13:21.033
idly by so as to never incur any

00:13:21.094 --> 00:13:21.514
guilt.

00:13:21.573 --> 00:13:23.235
It doesn't say anything to be a myth

00:13:23.275 --> 00:13:24.716
that people can say, well,

00:13:24.777 --> 00:13:25.898
my myth is perfect.

00:13:26.317 --> 00:13:27.919
I created my myth just perfect.

00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:29.100
No,

00:13:29.140 --> 00:13:31.043
there's no such thing as a perfect man.

00:13:31.082 --> 00:13:33.524
There's no such thing as a perfect animal.

00:13:35.062 --> 00:13:37.624
Perfection is not even something God is

00:13:37.764 --> 00:13:39.724
interested in because if we were perfect,

00:13:39.764 --> 00:13:41.125
we would not be interesting.

00:13:41.184 --> 00:13:43.024
If we were perfect, we could never grow.

00:13:43.044 --> 00:13:44.264
We could never learn anything.

00:13:44.304 --> 00:13:46.025
We could never experience anything new.

00:13:47.046 --> 00:13:50.226
And we could never prove that if mistaken,

00:13:50.267 --> 00:13:54.107
we could learn from our errors and grow

00:13:54.587 --> 00:13:55.227
as a result.

00:13:55.288 --> 00:13:58.089
And we could get up once fallen and

00:13:58.129 --> 00:14:01.710
again demonstrate that God can depend upon

00:14:01.789 --> 00:14:01.929
us.

00:14:03.870 --> 00:14:04.532
So therefore,

00:14:05.032 --> 00:14:08.774
Dowd became the Tamym lamb when he

00:14:08.894 --> 00:14:09.696
re-engaged,

00:14:09.796 --> 00:14:12.298
completing his calling by fulfilling Chag

00:14:12.337 --> 00:14:12.798
Matsah.

00:14:13.217 --> 00:14:16.000
When his Basar body was sacrificed as the

00:14:16.061 --> 00:14:16.461
lamb,

00:14:16.860 --> 00:14:19.923
he opened the door to eternal life for

00:14:19.943 --> 00:14:20.543
himself,

00:14:21.424 --> 00:14:23.666
in addition to the entire covenant family.

00:14:24.246 --> 00:14:25.368
And then on Matsah,

00:14:25.607 --> 00:14:27.850
when his nepesh soul carried our guilt

00:14:27.889 --> 00:14:31.472
into Sheowl to make us innocent before God.

00:14:32.369 --> 00:14:35.871
he was also carrying and offloading his

00:14:35.991 --> 00:14:36.231
own.

00:14:38.374 --> 00:14:41.096
The resolution that Yahowah had established

00:14:41.235 --> 00:14:45.239
in the Towrah applied to the Bikuwr,

00:14:45.499 --> 00:14:47.179
the firstborn son,

00:14:48.081 --> 00:14:49.621
as well as to all other Bikuwrym,

00:14:50.022 --> 00:14:50.923
firstborn children.

00:14:51.903 --> 00:14:53.245
God didn't change the rules.

00:14:53.504 --> 00:14:55.506
He simply applied them.

00:14:56.626 --> 00:14:57.807
Then working with Do,

00:14:57.847 --> 00:14:59.408
Yahowah enabled the benefits.

00:14:59.509 --> 00:15:00.750
That is the reason

00:15:01.788 --> 00:15:03.990
that Dowd would never die.

00:15:05.129 --> 00:15:07.671
He is the first of firstborn children.

00:15:09.491 --> 00:15:11.893
As a result of this pronouncement from

00:15:11.932 --> 00:15:12.253
God,

00:15:12.352 --> 00:15:15.053
the entire Christian New Testament must be

00:15:15.114 --> 00:15:15.595
rejected.

00:15:15.955 --> 00:15:18.596
Paul steals Dowd's titles and achievements

00:15:18.995 --> 00:15:20.836
and offers them to the fraud that is

00:15:20.897 --> 00:15:24.317
Jesus on the basis that the king was

00:15:24.398 --> 00:15:25.278
dead and buried.

00:15:25.619 --> 00:15:28.580
But that is not true.

00:15:31.186 --> 00:15:33.567
While Dowd would live by the rules of

00:15:33.628 --> 00:15:34.187
the Towrah,

00:15:34.248 --> 00:15:36.929
many would die for opting out of its

00:15:36.971 --> 00:15:38.692
guidance.

00:15:38.711 --> 00:15:41.653
This process would begin with the product

00:15:41.714 --> 00:15:46.477
of Dowd's gross impropriety.

00:15:46.498 --> 00:15:49.460
The lesson was meant to scream,

00:15:50.681 --> 00:15:54.923
I'll save you as my son when you

00:15:54.985 --> 00:15:56.765
return to the script.

00:15:57.937 --> 00:15:59.139
At that same time,

00:15:59.698 --> 00:16:03.760
I will impress upon you what happens when

00:16:03.780 --> 00:16:07.562
you write your own.

00:16:07.682 --> 00:16:09.224
That notwithstanding,

00:16:09.744 --> 00:16:12.684
because you spurned Yahowah,

00:16:12.725 --> 00:16:15.267
showing contempt for him in such an

00:16:15.506 --> 00:16:18.908
adversarial fashion with enmity and

00:16:19.048 --> 00:16:21.649
rancor, with word and deed,

00:16:22.549 --> 00:16:24.892
this child who is born to you

00:16:26.174 --> 00:16:30.778
will absolutely die.

00:16:30.798 --> 00:16:34.320
There would be no life as a result

00:16:35.880 --> 00:16:36.880
of spurning Yahowah,

00:16:38.282 --> 00:16:39.562
of showing contempt for him.

00:16:41.063 --> 00:16:43.424
And God wanted to make that absolutely

00:16:43.504 --> 00:16:45.886
clear to Dowd.

00:16:49.109 --> 00:16:51.570
And as such, well,

00:16:51.610 --> 00:16:53.051
this is the case with every soul.

00:16:54.517 --> 00:16:57.317
conceived in impropriety, treachery,

00:16:57.357 --> 00:16:57.878
and death.

00:16:59.499 --> 00:17:03.461
It would have been inexcusable for Dowd to

00:17:03.520 --> 00:17:05.721
cherish and reward the product of his

00:17:05.781 --> 00:17:09.143
sordid affair, of his deadly behavior,

00:17:09.603 --> 00:17:10.403
of his betrayal.

00:17:12.845 --> 00:17:14.525
What they did was reprehensible.

00:17:14.825 --> 00:17:17.747
It cannot be rewarded under any

00:17:17.866 --> 00:17:18.866
circumstances.

00:17:19.507 --> 00:17:21.928
And if Dowd did not receive this message

00:17:22.087 --> 00:17:23.169
loud and clear,

00:17:24.298 --> 00:17:25.780
we would all be as good as dead.

00:17:25.800 --> 00:17:28.226
Now, if you say, well,

00:17:28.567 --> 00:17:30.590
then if I'm extrapolating that,

00:17:30.651 --> 00:17:32.976
then you would say that the child of

00:17:33.237 --> 00:17:34.799
rape should die.

00:17:34.859 --> 00:17:35.280
No, I'm not.

00:17:37.713 --> 00:17:40.414
God doesn't know the rapist or the rape

00:17:40.454 --> 00:17:41.894
victim in all likelihood.

