La Natsach can also convey that this was

00:22:08.243 --> 00:22:12.425
written on behalf of the continually

00:22:12.506 --> 00:22:15.748
supervised, not just the eternal director,

00:22:16.548 --> 00:22:18.328
but it would be the eternal director

00:22:18.729 --> 00:22:20.609
continually supervising

00:22:21.982 --> 00:22:25.605
Dowd one way or another this would be

00:22:25.664 --> 00:22:28.446
consistent with the eighty-ninth Mizmowr

00:22:28.487 --> 00:22:30.708
where Yahowah admitted that he would be

00:22:30.768 --> 00:22:35.089
constantly keeping watch on him it is also

00:22:35.130 --> 00:22:37.872
the conclusion I drew from the last Mashal

00:22:38.751 --> 00:22:42.595
the Amah and herbal will be serving in

00:22:42.634 --> 00:22:47.277
this capacity and we have in the past

00:22:47.317 --> 00:22:48.798
and I think we will do so for

00:22:48.837 --> 00:22:49.659
at least the next

00:22:50.575 --> 00:22:51.575
One thousand years,

00:22:51.595 --> 00:22:54.195
the blink of an eye in your time.

00:22:55.757 --> 00:22:58.237
So perhaps I'm prejudiced in this regard,

00:22:58.678 --> 00:22:58.877
but.

00:23:00.278 --> 00:23:01.438
I'm put off.

00:23:03.019 --> 00:23:05.980
By anyone begging for forgiveness.

00:23:07.140 --> 00:23:08.359
That's how religions work.

00:23:09.740 --> 00:23:10.840
But not relationships.

00:23:12.741 --> 00:23:16.042
Stop doing the things that irritate God

00:23:16.462 --> 00:23:18.304
and then focus on what pleases them,

00:23:18.463 --> 00:23:19.743
that's the solution.

00:23:22.838 --> 00:23:25.381
Stop doing what irritates him and then

00:23:25.461 --> 00:23:26.961
start doing what pleases him.

00:23:27.561 --> 00:23:27.942
Simple.

00:23:28.342 --> 00:23:29.502
Don't beg for forgiveness.

00:23:30.463 --> 00:23:33.665
God has delineated the path to him.

00:23:34.286 --> 00:23:35.145
Follow the path.

00:23:36.467 --> 00:23:37.528
Listen to what he says.

00:23:37.788 --> 00:23:38.548
Act upon it.

00:23:39.429 --> 00:23:40.250
It's real simple.

00:23:41.009 --> 00:23:43.151
He is not going to do something special

00:23:43.191 --> 00:23:43.571
for you.

00:23:44.501 --> 00:23:46.542
You could beg until you're blue in the

00:23:46.583 --> 00:23:47.063
face,

00:23:47.604 --> 00:23:49.404
and all it's going to do is irritate

00:23:49.424 --> 00:23:49.664
him.

00:23:50.285 --> 00:23:54.067
He delineated a specific process to earn

00:23:54.086 --> 00:23:55.708
his trust and to become part of his

00:23:55.768 --> 00:23:56.548
covenant family.

00:23:57.128 --> 00:23:59.710
Follow it, accept it, acknowledge it,

00:23:59.869 --> 00:24:02.491
agree with it, or don't.

00:24:03.531 --> 00:24:06.053
But don't pretend that God's going to make

00:24:06.433 --> 00:24:09.035
an exception for you, because he's not.

00:24:10.096 --> 00:24:12.557
And that even includes Down.

00:24:14.481 --> 00:24:15.362
God's consistent.

00:24:15.642 --> 00:24:16.423
He's dependable.

00:24:17.002 --> 00:24:18.143
He laid out the plan.

00:24:18.682 --> 00:24:22.544
Either accept the plan or don't.

00:24:22.564 --> 00:24:25.065
But don't beg God to change it just

00:24:25.105 --> 00:24:26.045
because you want him to.

00:24:29.066 --> 00:24:33.787
Come to grips with what went wrong and

00:24:33.826 --> 00:24:36.488
clear away the obstacles that led to the

00:24:36.528 --> 00:24:37.268
misadventure.

00:24:38.228 --> 00:24:40.628
Show that you have learned from the

00:24:40.669 --> 00:24:41.148
mistake.

00:24:42.250 --> 00:24:45.614
by commencing corrective action.

00:24:46.535 --> 00:24:49.078
Sharpen your resolve and immediately

00:24:49.179 --> 00:24:51.402
re-engage in a productive way,

00:24:52.162 --> 00:24:53.884
better equipped and more resolute.

00:24:54.404 --> 00:24:56.468
I tell every friend that I've ever known

00:24:56.948 --> 00:24:58.190
who is going through an...

00:24:59.050 --> 00:25:01.692
depressing depressing circumstance where

00:25:02.053 --> 00:25:03.994
they think that the world has collapsed

00:25:04.035 --> 00:25:06.057
around them and they don't see any way

00:25:06.196 --> 00:25:08.397
out and woe is me and you know

00:25:08.518 --> 00:25:10.460
I just wish I wasn't even alive and

00:25:10.480 --> 00:25:11.800
they they just wallow in it and I

00:25:11.840 --> 00:25:16.904
said good grief man stop it get out

00:25:17.005 --> 00:25:17.826
of yourself

00:25:19.260 --> 00:25:22.063
The solution to depression is always the

00:25:22.123 --> 00:25:22.563
same.

00:25:23.243 --> 00:25:25.065
Get out of your stealth.

00:25:25.404 --> 00:25:28.067
Stop doing what brought you into that

00:25:28.106 --> 00:25:30.729
situation and start doing things that are

00:25:30.769 --> 00:25:31.509
worthwhile.

00:25:32.710 --> 00:25:36.271
Focus on helping somebody else accomplish

00:25:36.311 --> 00:25:37.432
something worthwhile.

00:25:37.512 --> 00:25:38.733
Make your life count.

00:25:39.413 --> 00:25:42.115
The moment you stop wallowing in misery

00:25:42.596 --> 00:25:44.857
and start acting in a way that is

00:25:44.917 --> 00:25:47.819
appropriate, that is conducive,

00:25:48.942 --> 00:25:50.423
and beneficial to others,

00:25:52.285 --> 00:25:55.208
your solution is before you.

00:25:55.748 --> 00:25:56.929
Your problem is solved.

00:25:59.010 --> 00:26:01.333
So, sharpen your resolve,

00:26:02.515 --> 00:26:04.155
re-engage in a productive way,

00:26:04.936 --> 00:26:07.278
always better equipped, more resolute,

00:26:07.699 --> 00:26:11.001
having been toughened up by having fallen

00:26:12.282 --> 00:26:14.105
and proving that you can get back up

00:26:14.184 --> 00:26:14.786
and go again.

00:26:16.637 --> 00:26:22.520
Turn the failure into an opportunity to

00:26:22.580 --> 00:26:23.340
rise above it.

00:26:24.981 --> 00:26:27.262
Stop wallowing in self-pity.

00:26:28.263 --> 00:26:31.164
Simply foreclose on the ensuing depression

00:26:31.586 --> 00:26:34.207
by turning your failure into a teaching

00:26:34.287 --> 00:26:37.127
opportunity so that you and others learn

00:26:37.167 --> 00:26:39.490
the lesson and don't make a similar

00:26:39.529 --> 00:26:40.069
mistake.

00:26:41.547 --> 00:26:43.367
You're not the first person that failed.

00:26:43.407 --> 00:26:44.867
You're not the first person that's been

00:26:44.907 --> 00:26:45.567
disappointed.

00:26:45.688 --> 00:26:46.769
Get over yourself.

00:26:48.449 --> 00:26:54.652
Prove to yourself, to those who know you,

00:26:54.951 --> 00:26:56.372
and to Yahowah,

00:26:56.412 --> 00:26:59.792
that you can stop being annoying and that

00:26:59.813 --> 00:27:01.453
you can get up and get going,

00:27:02.334 --> 00:27:05.535
lifting the tide rather than riding it out

00:27:05.575 --> 00:27:06.194
to sea.

00:27:08.736 --> 00:27:10.076
It really all gets back to Eden.

00:27:10.961 --> 00:27:11.522
and to Adam.

00:27:12.864 --> 00:27:16.067
He climbed up in the tree and tried

00:27:16.106 --> 00:27:20.250
to hide within it rather than disengaging

00:27:20.310 --> 00:27:22.673
from that which was opposed to Yahowah's

00:27:22.713 --> 00:27:23.394
instructions.

00:27:24.214 --> 00:27:26.657
He begged for clemency by failing to be

00:27:26.698 --> 00:27:27.258
accountable.

00:27:28.219 --> 00:27:31.102
He not only failed to cease irritating God

00:27:31.162 --> 00:27:33.183
and failed to learn anything from his poor

00:27:33.243 --> 00:27:33.664
judgment,

00:27:34.266 --> 00:27:37.508
There was no attempt at all to improve,

00:27:37.909 --> 00:27:39.490
to get out of his own head and

00:27:39.509 --> 00:27:43.353
to do something that showed Yahowah that he

00:27:43.373 --> 00:27:47.395
could be trusted.

00:27:47.415 --> 00:27:50.478
Dowd was in the woe is me phase,

00:27:50.577 --> 00:27:53.961
begging for forgiveness rather than doing

00:27:54.000 --> 00:27:59.625
the things to earn it.

00:27:59.664 --> 00:28:01.145
If I've hurt your little feelings,

00:28:01.326 --> 00:28:02.067
I'm not sorry.

00:28:03.569 --> 00:28:07.510
This is a life lesson that would serve

00:28:07.671 --> 00:28:10.971
all of those on antidepressant medicines.

00:28:12.393 --> 00:28:14.452
Stop depending on chemicals.

00:28:15.073 --> 00:28:17.513
Stop depending on the psychiatrist.

00:28:17.834 --> 00:28:19.855
Stop wallowing in your pity.

00:28:19.894 --> 00:28:21.494
Stop being miserable.

00:28:22.596 --> 00:28:23.915
Do something worthwhile.

00:28:27.542 --> 00:28:29.884
You should choose to be merciful to me.

00:28:30.044 --> 00:28:32.104
He said, you should choose to be merciful.

00:28:32.144 --> 00:28:35.184
You should want to pity me while electing

00:28:35.224 --> 00:28:40.086
to favor me because it's imperative that

00:28:40.586 --> 00:28:44.907
you remain inclined toward me.

00:28:44.928 --> 00:28:45.689
chanan any',

00:28:46.388 --> 00:28:48.348
you want to be kind to me because

00:28:48.409 --> 00:28:52.230
it is essential that you show me some

00:28:52.290 --> 00:28:53.030
compassion.

00:28:54.585 --> 00:28:57.286
Call imperative, second person,

00:28:57.826 --> 00:28:59.387
masculine singular.

00:29:00.788 --> 00:29:02.148
Elohim, God,

00:29:02.909 --> 00:29:05.270
in the manner of your loyal love,

00:29:05.310 --> 00:29:08.211
your unfailing kindness and deep devotion,

00:29:08.632 --> 00:29:12.513
your unwavering favoritism,

00:29:12.693 --> 00:29:15.496
and consistent with your compassion and

00:29:15.556 --> 00:29:16.556
tender affection.

00:29:17.696 --> 00:29:18.297
You must,

00:29:18.436 --> 00:29:20.558
or at the very least you should want

00:29:20.598 --> 00:29:20.778
to,

00:29:21.788 --> 00:29:24.251
Blot out and wipe away my pesha,

00:29:25.031 --> 00:29:28.736
my rebellion and revolting defiance as I

00:29:28.796 --> 00:29:29.856
breached the agreement.

00:29:31.098 --> 00:29:32.480
My hostile stance,

00:29:33.060 --> 00:29:37.384
my indignance and mutinous insurgency as I

00:29:37.444 --> 00:29:40.008
reneged on my commitment and I rejected

00:29:40.107 --> 00:29:42.630
our alliance.

00:29:42.650 --> 00:29:44.992
Psalm fifty one one.

00:29:51.527 --> 00:29:57.112
Dowd, at his best, is a master linguist.

00:29:59.012 --> 00:30:02.477
He uses the Hebrew language with great

00:30:02.517 --> 00:30:02.916
aplomb,

00:30:04.198 --> 00:30:06.259
particularly when it comes to moods.

00:30:07.601 --> 00:30:09.563
And for those who do not know,

00:30:09.702 --> 00:30:13.566
Hebrew is unique in that there are three

00:30:14.027 --> 00:30:16.167
volitional moods in the Hebrew language.

00:30:17.045 --> 00:30:19.006
The cohortative speaks of first-person

00:30:19.046 --> 00:30:19.507
volition.

00:30:20.126 --> 00:30:21.607
I want you to forgive me.

00:30:22.008 --> 00:30:24.028
I want you to be inclined favorably to

00:30:24.108 --> 00:30:24.189
me.

00:30:24.529 --> 00:30:26.029
If he had said that, that's fine.

00:30:26.671 --> 00:30:28.311
Wouldn't have mattered, but it's still,

00:30:28.491 --> 00:30:29.792
it would have been fine.

00:30:31.334 --> 00:30:32.795
First-person expression of volition,

00:30:32.815 --> 00:30:34.635
the cohortative, that's not what this was.

00:30:35.355 --> 00:30:36.737
It was written in the imperative.

00:30:38.595 --> 00:30:39.596
The imperative can be,

00:30:39.756 --> 00:30:41.916
as the name suggests, a command.

00:30:42.438 --> 00:30:45.680
I'm ordering you, commanding you,

00:30:45.759 --> 00:30:48.902
demanding that you are merciful to me.

00:30:48.922 --> 00:30:55.686
Yeah, that's not going to work with God.

00:30:55.707 --> 00:30:58.249
The imperative move is often used as a

00:30:58.308 --> 00:31:00.330
hypothetical with a possibility.

00:31:01.010 --> 00:31:02.632
Maybe you should consider...

00:31:03.848 --> 00:31:06.191
even though the odds are not likely or

00:31:06.230 --> 00:31:11.636
great, that you should treat me favorably.

00:31:11.676 --> 00:31:13.838
That's not good either, is it?

00:31:13.878 --> 00:31:15.400
And I'm here to tell you that while

00:31:15.440 --> 00:31:18.542
there are times when you can project on

00:31:18.583 --> 00:31:21.506
Yahowah his will, you can say, Yahowah,

00:31:21.526 --> 00:31:22.467
I know this is what you want to

00:31:22.487 --> 00:31:24.189
do.

00:31:24.209 --> 00:31:25.150
Because you've said so.

00:31:26.692 --> 00:31:29.273
And so you can project second-person

00:31:29.334 --> 00:31:30.634
volition on God,

00:31:31.255 --> 00:31:33.977
but doing so in this circumstance and

00:31:33.997 --> 00:31:34.156
saying,

00:31:34.517 --> 00:31:36.077
you need to do this because of who

00:31:36.117 --> 00:31:40.400
you are, when I've been a jerk, no.

00:31:41.720 --> 00:31:43.040
So I want you to know that that's

00:31:43.101 --> 00:31:44.942
why I wrote this as I did.

00:31:44.961 --> 00:31:48.442
You should choose to be merciful to me.

00:31:48.462 --> 00:31:50.544
The imperative as volitional,

00:31:50.604 --> 00:31:53.365
the second person, wanting to pity me,

00:31:53.405 --> 00:31:53.605
same.

00:31:54.618 --> 00:31:55.859
While electing to favor me.

00:31:55.920 --> 00:31:59.662
Because it's imperative.

00:31:59.682 --> 00:32:01.182
That you remain inclined to me.

00:32:01.202 --> 00:32:01.784
Or at least.

00:32:02.544 --> 00:32:07.207
Demonstrate that possibility.

00:32:07.326 --> 00:32:09.148
And he says.

00:32:10.108 --> 00:32:10.509
Elohim.

00:32:10.529 --> 00:32:13.892
God.

00:32:13.912 --> 00:32:16.212
No problem using the title Elohim.

00:32:16.453 --> 00:32:16.993
On occasion.

00:32:18.855 --> 00:32:19.234
But not.

00:32:19.855 --> 00:32:21.037
In an opening request.

00:32:21.596 --> 00:32:23.097
Not if you're projecting.

00:32:24.038 --> 00:32:24.318
Your.

00:32:26.268 --> 00:32:28.049
impressions of what God should want on

00:32:28.089 --> 00:32:28.289
him.

00:32:29.230 --> 00:32:29.891
He has a name.

00:32:29.931 --> 00:32:30.471
Dowd knows it.

00:32:30.530 --> 00:32:32.653
Dowd uses it more frequently than anybody

00:32:32.712 --> 00:32:32.893
else.

00:32:33.753 --> 00:32:39.076
In this, the fifty-first Mizmowr,

00:32:40.979 --> 00:32:43.240
it's the only one where Dowd never

00:32:43.339 --> 00:32:44.441
mentions Yahowah's name.

00:32:45.521 --> 00:32:50.945
He is so full of himself, so lost,

00:32:51.086 --> 00:32:51.986
so depressed,

00:32:53.287 --> 00:32:54.367
so embarrassed that

00:32:55.116 --> 00:33:00.320
He won't even say Yahowah's name.

00:33:00.401 --> 00:33:02.542
It's Elohim.

00:33:02.583 --> 00:33:04.003
And that won't change all the way through.

00:33:06.385 --> 00:33:08.028
And then he is projecting all of this

00:33:08.087 --> 00:33:11.069
based upon what Yahowah will want to do

00:33:11.130 --> 00:33:11.931
or must do,

00:33:13.352 --> 00:33:16.674
even though it's Dowd's Pasha rebellion,

00:33:17.476 --> 00:33:18.455
revolting defiance,

00:33:18.496 --> 00:33:19.958
because he's the one that breached the

00:33:19.978 --> 00:33:20.357
agreement.

00:33:22.596 --> 00:33:23.176
So as I've said,

00:33:23.217 --> 00:33:24.877
when it comes to the imperative mood,

00:33:25.058 --> 00:33:26.659
we have three options.

00:33:26.779 --> 00:33:29.181
It is either being used to issue a

00:33:29.240 --> 00:33:31.903
mandate, like a command,

00:33:33.262 --> 00:33:35.585
stating something that you are demanding,

00:33:36.505 --> 00:33:39.487
stating that which is imperative.

00:33:40.847 --> 00:33:43.209
It can be an indication of the will

00:33:43.390 --> 00:33:45.131
of the individual being dressed,

00:33:45.931 --> 00:33:48.732
or it can be a hypothetical.

00:33:49.403 --> 00:33:51.844
saying that there is the mere possibility,

00:33:51.903 --> 00:33:53.423
even though it's not a likelihood,

00:33:54.644 --> 00:33:56.044
that you're going to do this, that,

00:33:56.084 --> 00:33:56.743
or the other thing.

00:33:58.545 --> 00:33:59.545
However, in this case,

00:33:59.845 --> 00:34:03.006
all three approaches are not only wrong,

00:34:04.405 --> 00:34:07.287
they miss the point.

00:34:07.406 --> 00:34:09.706
It's Dowd who wants Yahowah to forgive and

00:34:09.746 --> 00:34:11.306
forget.

00:34:11.327 --> 00:34:12.807
To express that sentiment,

00:34:13.387 --> 00:34:15.248
he should have conveyed his plea in the

00:34:15.288 --> 00:34:16.288
cohortative mood,

00:34:16.427 --> 00:34:19.088
conveying first-person volition, his will.

00:34:20.302 --> 00:34:22.643
God has clearly stated his position on

00:34:22.682 --> 00:34:22.943
this,

00:34:23.903 --> 00:34:25.704
which is that he is exceedingly

00:34:25.744 --> 00:34:26.425
disappointed.

00:34:26.985 --> 00:34:28.206
He is disgusted.

00:34:29.547 --> 00:34:34.010
And that there would be no ongoing or

00:34:34.050 --> 00:34:35.110
immediate remedy,

00:34:36.030 --> 00:34:39.251
that the remedy was Passover a thousand

00:34:39.271 --> 00:34:40.253
years from now.

00:34:41.994 --> 00:34:44.255
And that the consequence to Dowd and to

00:34:44.295 --> 00:34:47.657
his people would be severe.

00:34:48.056 --> 00:34:49.057
He's pronounced judgment.

00:34:50.250 --> 00:34:50.929
He's not going to say, oh, well,

00:34:50.949 --> 00:34:52.351
let's just forget about that.

00:34:52.751 --> 00:34:53.952
I didn't really mean what I said.

00:34:55.833 --> 00:34:55.952
No,

00:34:55.972 --> 00:34:59.673
a God who forgives those who beg for

00:34:59.733 --> 00:34:59.855
it,

00:35:01.195 --> 00:35:02.896
it bears no resemblance to the God of

00:35:02.936 --> 00:35:03.376
the Towrah.

00:35:04.376 --> 00:35:06.117
A God whose will is bent by the

00:35:06.157 --> 00:35:10.259
demands of men is a religious construct.

00:35:11.760 --> 00:35:13.340
You might like the way that sounds,

00:35:14.240 --> 00:35:15.782
but it's repulsive to the real God.

00:35:17.880 --> 00:35:18.922
Yahowah's not all loving,

00:35:19.702 --> 00:35:22.865
nor is he always kind and merciful.

00:35:23.246 --> 00:35:23.585
You know,

00:35:23.646 --> 00:35:27.108
I saw the big billboard at the Super

00:35:27.148 --> 00:35:29.972
Bowl halftime that, you know,

00:35:30.072 --> 00:35:33.074
that love is the only thing that is

00:35:33.155 --> 00:35:34.476
more powerful than hate.

00:35:35.157 --> 00:35:40.501
And it conveys a largely inaccurate

00:35:40.641 --> 00:35:43.443
message.

00:35:43.463 --> 00:35:44.445
To love one must hate.

00:35:47.670 --> 00:35:48.692
It's true.

00:35:48.711 --> 00:35:49.351
Hate is a virtue.

00:35:50.914 --> 00:35:52.534
You need to know who to hate,

00:35:52.574 --> 00:35:54.396
why to hate, when to hate.

00:35:57.179 --> 00:35:57.920
And if you don't,

00:35:58.199 --> 00:35:59.440
then you really can't be loving.

00:36:01.563 --> 00:36:03.985
It is essential that we hate what Doe

00:36:04.025 --> 00:36:05.726
did.

00:36:05.786 --> 00:36:07.347
Murder.

00:36:07.427 --> 00:36:07.788
Rape.

00:36:09.570 --> 00:36:10.791
He had become an alcoholic.

00:36:12.512 --> 00:36:12.932
He was...

00:36:14.451 --> 00:36:16.251
compromising everyone.

00:36:16.693 --> 00:36:20.135
He was leading an exceedingly deceptive

00:36:20.596 --> 00:36:20.956
plot.

00:36:21.036 --> 00:36:24.318
He was forsaking his responsibility as a

00:36:24.358 --> 00:36:25.139
leader of his people.

00:36:25.159 --> 00:36:26.099
We ought to despise that.

00:36:26.481 --> 00:36:30.242
The consequences were grievous.

00:36:30.264 --> 00:36:33.925
We ought to hate rape and rapists,

00:36:34.646 --> 00:36:36.748
incest and those who perpetrated,

00:36:37.528 --> 00:36:38.809
pedophilia and pedophiles.

00:36:38.829 --> 00:36:40.851
We ought to hate those things.

00:36:42.605 --> 00:36:43.905
We ought to hate mass murderers,

00:36:44.005 --> 00:36:46.527
terrorists.

00:36:47.068 --> 00:36:49.088
If you don't hate those things that

00:36:50.090 --> 00:36:52.990
inspire universal bad behavior,

00:36:53.050 --> 00:36:56.193
like jihad, Islamic terrorism,

00:36:57.034 --> 00:36:59.295
then you're being merciless to the

00:36:59.315 --> 00:37:01.797
innocent.

00:37:01.836 --> 00:37:03.378
You're not being compassionate to them.

00:37:05.518 --> 00:37:07.039
And that's why Yahowah's not all loving.

00:37:09.061 --> 00:37:11.483
He can't be and to be loving at

00:37:11.543 --> 00:37:11.682
all.

00:37:12.713 --> 00:37:13.655
If you're all loving,

00:37:15.376 --> 00:37:17.817
you're just fooling everyone.

00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:20.139
Because to love,

00:37:20.918 --> 00:37:22.599
you must hate that which is threatening to

00:37:22.659 --> 00:37:23.860
those you do love.

00:37:25.561 --> 00:37:27.103
And if we were all loving,

00:37:27.143 --> 00:37:28.543
there would be no purpose to life,

00:37:28.623 --> 00:37:29.884
no rules to live by,

00:37:29.943 --> 00:37:31.344
no guidance to gain from,

00:37:31.405 --> 00:37:32.585
no lessons to learn.

00:37:34.706 --> 00:37:37.989
We can choose to learn and to do

00:37:38.028 --> 00:37:40.010
the will of God,

00:37:40.050 --> 00:37:42.092
but we cannot impose our will on him.

00:37:43.601 --> 00:37:47.083
We do well to follow his advice and

00:37:47.123 --> 00:37:49.664
embarrass ourselves when we offload our

00:37:49.704 --> 00:37:53.407
counsel and requests on him.

00:37:53.427 --> 00:37:55.329
It's very seldom that I will say, God,

00:37:55.369 --> 00:37:56.568
you need to give me this.

00:37:56.989 --> 00:37:57.650
I want that.

00:37:58.530 --> 00:37:59.831
I don't have something or other.

00:38:00.512 --> 00:38:01.373
Occasionally I'll say, you know,

00:38:01.472 --> 00:38:02.253
I don't get this.

00:38:02.833 --> 00:38:04.213
I would really appreciate it.

00:38:04.233 --> 00:38:05.835
Maybe if you'd lead me in the right

00:38:05.876 --> 00:38:07.416
direction, I can figure this out.

00:38:07.476 --> 00:38:09.197
Yeah, I need a little help here.

00:38:09.998 --> 00:38:12.362
or when things go awry in the midst

00:38:12.422 --> 00:38:13.824
of carrying out our mission.

00:38:13.903 --> 00:38:14.344
And, you know,

00:38:14.364 --> 00:38:15.947
I know he wants us to do a

00:38:15.987 --> 00:38:18.769
good job of conveying his testimony at

00:38:18.809 --> 00:38:19.311
this time.

00:38:20.012 --> 00:38:21.574
And something's come up that's making it

00:38:21.653 --> 00:38:22.456
very difficult.

00:38:22.476 --> 00:38:23.836
I'll come to him and say,

00:38:24.297 --> 00:38:25.480
I don't know the answer to this one.

00:38:27.061 --> 00:38:27.342
Help me.

00:38:28.043 --> 00:38:29.063
I'm sure you've written about it.

00:38:29.264 --> 00:38:30.284
Tell me where you've written about it,

00:38:30.304 --> 00:38:33.146
and I'll go translate it and try to

00:38:33.206 --> 00:38:33.927
understand it.

00:38:34.007 --> 00:38:37.150
But I'm not telling God to give me

00:38:37.210 --> 00:38:39.572
something that he's already committed to

00:38:39.612 --> 00:38:39.952
doing.

00:38:40.813 --> 00:38:45.338
Never ask God once to save me.

00:38:45.498 --> 00:38:46.318
It's superfluous.

00:38:47.619 --> 00:38:48.920
I want to do this job well,

00:38:49.380 --> 00:38:51.282
and I know the result of that.

00:38:52.199 --> 00:38:54.900
He laid out the terms and conditions of

00:38:55.161 --> 00:38:57.081
our being part of the covenant family,

00:38:57.141 --> 00:38:58.422
and I have met them.

00:38:58.543 --> 00:39:00.603
That means that it's a fait accompli.

00:39:00.643 --> 00:39:03.144
Why ask for that which he's already

00:39:03.184 --> 00:39:04.065
committed to doing?

00:39:06.567 --> 00:39:07.367
So in my view,

00:39:09.168 --> 00:39:12.771
just because our king had become pitiful

00:39:12.791 --> 00:39:18.693
did not mean that he engendered pity.

00:39:18.733 --> 00:39:19.715
Having shown none,

00:39:21.226 --> 00:39:23.307
He was currently the last person on the

00:39:23.347 --> 00:39:27.451
planet deserving compassion.

00:39:27.510 --> 00:39:28.873
Now I want you to think that through.

00:39:29.713 --> 00:39:32.054
God had just affirmed what I have told

00:39:32.094 --> 00:39:32.275
you.

00:39:32.976 --> 00:39:37.179
He said, because you showed no compassion,

00:39:37.219 --> 00:39:41.003
this is the consequence.

00:39:41.063 --> 00:39:44.525
So here's a man who had shown no

00:39:44.585 --> 00:39:46.847
compassion for anybody.

00:39:49.451 --> 00:39:51.371
And now he was begging for compassion.

00:39:51.952 --> 00:39:53.132
That's revolting.

00:39:53.271 --> 00:39:54.512
That's pathetic.

00:39:55.572 --> 00:39:56.793
So having shown none,

00:39:57.452 --> 00:39:59.653
he was the last person on the planet

00:39:59.873 --> 00:40:02.454
deserving of it.

00:40:02.534 --> 00:40:08.177
And to beg God for it is pitiful.

00:40:09.317 --> 00:40:12.137
I'm telling you, I love my king.

00:40:13.777 --> 00:40:17.059
And indeed my surrogate son.

00:40:17.139 --> 00:40:18.460
And I will lay down my life for

00:40:18.500 --> 00:40:18.599
him.

00:40:19.875 --> 00:40:22.856
Because I know the good outweighs the bad.

00:40:23.177 --> 00:40:27.237
The right triumphs over the wrong.

00:40:27.278 --> 00:40:29.378
But I'm going to be forthright because

00:40:29.420 --> 00:40:33.141
it's in his interest and yours to know

00:40:33.161 --> 00:40:36.523
when he's wrong.

00:40:36.543 --> 00:40:38.063
And I'm here to tell you that what

00:40:38.123 --> 00:40:39.603
I'm telling you now,

00:40:39.844 --> 00:40:43.126
I told him emphatically.

00:40:45.956 --> 00:40:49.376
So since God shared this with us,

00:40:49.416 --> 00:40:52.257
since Dowd wrote these words,

00:40:53.559 --> 00:40:56.059
we're going to have a confrontation here

00:40:56.139 --> 00:40:57.239
now, and I'm not backing down.

00:40:58.019 --> 00:40:58.579
And by the way,

00:40:58.619 --> 00:41:00.280
he wouldn't respect me if I did.

00:41:03.382 --> 00:41:05.182
So the only thing in that opening

00:41:05.222 --> 00:41:07.264
statement that Dowd got right was Pesha.

00:41:08.503 --> 00:41:09.684
He had breached the agreement.

00:41:10.065 --> 00:41:13.666
He had overtly rebelled against Yahowah.

00:41:14.608 --> 00:41:16.568
His behavior was indignant.

00:41:17.510 --> 00:41:18.791
It was treasonous.

00:41:18.871 --> 00:41:20.211
It was mutinous.

00:41:22.213 --> 00:41:24.976
But it wasn't all in the past.

00:41:25.576 --> 00:41:27.416
He was still laying with Bathsheba.

00:41:28.577 --> 00:41:30.519
He was pining over the product of their

00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:32.961
treasonous and appalling behavior.

00:41:33.782 --> 00:41:35.983
He was lounging around all day feeling

00:41:36.103 --> 00:41:37.405
sorry for himself.

00:41:38.125 --> 00:41:40.246
It was so bad.

00:41:41.755 --> 00:41:44.697
Dowd couldn't even say Yahowah's name.

00:41:48.860 --> 00:41:49.800
